The above features, advantages and objectives of the present invention will more fully be appreciated through the following detailed discussion, reference being made to the drawing in which:


FIG. 1 is a plan perspective view of the fly trap in its pre-assembled package;


FIG. 2 is an exploded plan perspective view similar to FIG. 1 but also illustrating the scroll tube, wound web and support wire lodged within a cylinder;


FIG. 3 is a plan perspective view of the fly trap in its assembled form;


FIG. 3a is a cross-sectional view along line 3a--3a of FIG. 3;


FIG. 4 is a partial cross-sectional view along line 4--4 of FIG. 3;


FIG. 4a is a partial view showing a fisherman knot alternative connection to the support wire;


FIG. 5 is a cross-sectional view through the scroll tube along line 5--5 of FIG. 3;


FIG. 6 is a cross-sectional view of the cylinder taken along line 6--6 of FIG. 3;


FIG. 7 is a partial cross-sectional view of the scroll tube taken along line 7--7 of FIG. 3 shown to illustrate the detent;


FIG. 8 is a view of the clip arrangement securing the web to the cylinder taken along line 8--8 of FIG. 3 and shown in enlarged partial view;


FIG. 9 is an exploded view of an end of the scroll tube, the cap, the L-shaped connector and terminus with eyelet of the support wire; and


FIGS. 10-12 are views showing the mounting the trap in horizontal arrangements along a ceiling area.
